<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/2457511-stebbins"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1556276374i/2457511._UY100_CR21,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/2457511-stebbins">Stebbins</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">You&apos;re confusing science for technology. It seems obvious that the scientific principles underlying the technology are the same today as they were the<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">You're confusing science for technology. It seems obvious that the scientific principles underlying the technology are the same today as they were then, even if technology you speak of itself didn't exist at the time of the book's writing.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
